"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-24-paris-living-olympic-dream-city-feels-like-a-jail-21282851\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Squadrons ofsoldiers draftedfrom all overFrance; anAI surveillancesystem that would makeChina's president Xi Jinping jealous; both banks ofthe River Seinebarricaded.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 106, \"end\": 116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Xi Jinping\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Xi_Jinping\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This isParisdays before the 2024OlympicGames, which kick off this Friday, July 26.\", \"from\": 167, \"to\": 249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To anyone who does not live in a large European city likeLondon, Paris - often referred to as the 'City of Love' - might resemble adystopian enclavepreparing for the Hunger Games.\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 316, \"end\": 321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.294795464131326e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yasmina, general manager at Hotel Des Ducs D'Anjou, just a few minutes from the Louvre Museum, said the city 'feels like a jail' right now.\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 475, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D'Anjou\", \"score\": 0.9999998023099774, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"D'Anjou\", \"types\": [\"Q756\", \"Q4886\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D'Anjou\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/D'Anjou\"}, {\"begin\": 512, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She told Metro.co.uk: 'On every street there are at least four or five police officers.\", \"from\": 573, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'It feels unsafe.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To me, the presence of so many police means there is a threat of a terrorist attack.'\", \"from\": 680, \"to\": 765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tbrowser thatsupports HTML5 \\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\tvideo  Up Next  Arriving at Gare Du Nord, there are no flags or posters to signal thatthe Olympicsare 72 hours away.\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.602098009084261e-20, \"text\": \"JavaScript\", \"types\": [\"Q9143\", \"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/JavaScript\"}, {\"begin\": 872, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.688925753614917e-15, \"text\": \"HTML5\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/HTML5\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is only when you get closer to the Seine that the police presence becomes more noticeable, particularly around attractions and monuments like the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1042, \"end\": 1047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.50424790254246e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a year ago that the head of the 2024 Olympic Games organising committee, Tony Estanguet, declared that Paris will be 'the safest city in the world' when the event starts.\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.294795464131326e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, this\\u00a0prediction looks more convincing.\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1392, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A 'no-go' grey zone - something like an iron curtain - has been erected in the heart of the city, making it inaccessible to both residents and tourists without avalid QR code.\", \"from\": 1394, \"to\": 1569, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Also known as a 'Games Pass', it allows entry to the perimeter - but the system to get one is complicated and has led to a lot of confusion.\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Visitors have also been advised to apply more than a week before arriving.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Barriers were first put in place on July 18, a full week before the Games opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1879, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This has been a surprise - and has resulted in a lot of frustration.\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1948, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mevhibe and Kilian, a couple from Germany who were on their first trip to Paris, were not aware that the Olympics were taking place.\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Kilian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8166684093863726e-14, \"text\": \"Kilian\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Kilian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Kilian\"}, {\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.294795464131326e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They did not know that they were expected to get a code to access some of the city's main attractions and river banks.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'All of the roadblocks are very annoying and we did not know that we have to get a pass in advance,' Mevhibe told Metro.co.uk.\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2317, \"end\": 2328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We cannot access the Seine and we have to make big circles to get to anything.\", \"from\": 2331, \"to\": 2410, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2353, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.50424790254246e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'We wanted to walk from Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay to Notre Dame, but it is not possible.\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2449, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"score\": 0.9999999943702278, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We had tickets, but still we could not go.'\", \"from\": 2489, \"to\": 2532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quel sentiment atroce de se retrouver en cage dans son propre quartier.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2580, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"dans\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/State_Agency_for_National_Security\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alors que ces JO \\u00c3\\u00a9taient cens\\u00c3\\u00a9s \\u00c3\\u00aatre populaires, les parisiens, consid\\u00c3\\u00a9r\\u00c3\\u00a9s comme quantit\\u00c3\\u00a9s n\\u00c3\\u00a9gligeables, en sont exclus.\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"J\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ose \\u00c3\\u00a0 peine imaginer l\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099enfer pour les personnes \\u00c3\\u00a0 mobilit\\u00c3\\u00a9 r\\u00c3\\u00a9duite.#saccageparispic.twitter.com/XLvAZnlaEb  Lines of police officers guard the barricades lining the Seine, scanning code after a code for anyone who wants to enter.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2909, \"end\": 2914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.50424790254246e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At every crossing, there are people pleading to be let through, without much success.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Metro.co.uk interviewed one police officer, who wished to remain anonymous, who was stationed outside the Notre Dame, on\\u00a0\\u00cele de la Cit\\u00e9.\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3198, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3062, \"end\": 3073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"score\": 0.9993608704168107, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Metro.co.uk\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metro_(British_newspaper)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They said that in the last 50 minutes, they had scanned more than 200 passes, but had only allowed entry to two.\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a lot of cases, people are asked to produce additional documentation like a pre-booked ticket to a museum, a reservation to a restaurant or an appointment to a hospital.\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Hundreds of people turn up every day without a code,' they said.\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3553, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'The issue is that they do not know they need a code.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3607, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tourists and residents.\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Normally, even if they have a ticket to see an attraction inside the zone, they are not allowed if they do not have a code.\", \"from\": 3633, \"to\": 3757, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I feel bad, so I let them through.'\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The militarised approach to the Olympics is not without reason.\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A series ofextremist attackshave rocked Paris and other 